title.label: Bugs hold a great game back

content.label: I bought this game so that I could play with my son and wife in head to head matchups. The writing, look, and most of the play style is spot on. Unfortunately, the create a friend and play a friend function has been totally broken, so we‚Äôve only been able to play one player versions. This was a huge disappointment after a lot of time investment. The game has a lot of nagging bugs that are frustrating. In addition to freezes that can occur in battles, there are more obvious and simple issues. For instance the Radical Cyborg I use as my player isn‚Äôt considered a Teen Titan or Justice League member but the other Cyborgs are‚Äî and the other Radical Titans are considered Titans. It‚Äôs a sort of obvious bug that is frustrating because it changes the play experience. My wife is Raven and she continually gets huge bonuses in battles, but my player is literally at a disadvantage. Other issues involve quests, like my Cheetah in Metropolis doesn‚Äôt show a star and is mostly non respond. This game would be five star if it did a better job of testing its bugs. I especially love the writing and vocal performances. It nails what makes the show great, so the technical issues are a remarkable disappointment.
